## Question

On mbed 3 the "ualloc" yotta module was used for _malloc_ and _free_ implementation. This allowed us to enable and customise an UART trace, allowing us to study the dynamic memory performance our code and look for optimisations. E.g.

``` C++
void *mbed_ualloc(size_t bytes, UAllocTraits_t traits, void *cb_caller)
{
    void *caller;
    if (cb_caller == NULL) {
        caller = (void*)caller_addr();
    } else {
        caller = cb_caller;
    }
    void *p = mbed_ualloc_internal(bytes, traits, caller);
    if (!prevent_tracing) {
        prevent_tracing = 1;
        ualloc_debug(UALLOC_DEBUG_LOG, "ua c:%p s:%u m:%p\n", caller, (unsigned)bytes, p);
        prevent_tracing = 0;
    }
    return p;
}
```

So far I could not figure out how to replicate this in mbed5. Is this memory tracing still a possibility?

